<subSubSection id="C3796513FFE9FFF6FCF4F8E3FDDB11DE" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BDC3698FFE9FFF6FCF4F8E3FDDB11DE" blockId="1.[794,1418,1914,2131]" lastBlockId="2.[170,795,218,435]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFE9FFF5FCF4F8E3FC4F17FE" bold="true" box="[794,925,1914,1939]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Type data:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFE9FFF5FC45F8E3FBAA17FE" author="Schrottky, C." box="[939,1144,1914,1939]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="330 - 613" refId="ref4893" refString="Schrottky, C. 1902 b. Ensaio sobre as abelhas solitarias do Brazil. Revista do Museu Paulista, 5: 330 - 613." type="journal article" year="1902">Schrottky (1902b)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from a couple of males collected by Wilhelm Ehrhardt in Rincão, southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFE9FFF5FBE2F823FB9817BE" box="[1036,1098,1978,2003]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Ehrhardt (1860‑1936) was a Guyana‑born German animal collector and an excellent taxidermist that operated in 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFE9FFF5FBB0F863FB48187E" box="[1118,1178,2042,2067]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
around the early 20 
<superScript id="7C169BD0FFE9FFF5FA95F860FA5B1865" attach="none" box="[1403,1417,2041,2056]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">th</superScript>
century. He collected thousands of specimens of various animal groups, among them some amphibian, fish, mammal and insect species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FE1FFF43FD06109E" author="Gutsche, A. &amp; Kwet, A. &amp; Kucharzewski, C. &amp; Lingnau, R. &amp; Gunther, R." box="[497,724,218,243]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="80 - 93" refId="ref4123" refString="Gutsche, A.; Kwet, A.; Kucharzewski, C.; Lingnau, R. &amp; Gunther, R. 2007. Wilhelm Ehrhardt and an evaluation of his amphibians and reptiles held in the Herpetological Collection of the Museum fur Naturkunde, Berlin. Zoosystematics and Evolution, 83 (1): 80 - 93. DOI" type="journal article" year="2007">
Gutsche 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FDB8FF43FD43109E" box="[598,657,218,243]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.,</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). Both 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFEAFFF6FF44FF63FEDF117E" box="[170,269,250,275]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">syntypes</typeStatus>
are housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5DFFEAFFF6FE26FF63FDDA117E" box="[456,520,250,275]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="Museum">MZSP</collectionCode>
being here designated the 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFEAFFF6FF38FE83FEED115E" box="[214,319,282,307]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">lectotype</typeStatus>
the one in best condition (
<figureCitation id="13582A1DFFEAFFF6FD82FE83FD32115E" box="[620,736,282,307]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[94,153,1454,1479]" captionTargetBox="[94,1407,857,1424]" captionTargetId="figure-55@3.[94,1417,857,1424]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Centrisehrhardti Schrottky,1902 (lectotype male).(A) Head,frontal view (scale bar: 2 mm).(B) Habitus,dorsal view (scale bar: 5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614964" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614964/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs. 2A, B</figureCitation>
). The specimen has the following data label: 97250 [printed]\ 1360 [handwritten]\ 
<specimenCount id="9D65FD11FFEAFFF6FE4FFEC3FE66111C" box="[417,436,346,369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
[handwritten]. The 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFEAFFF6FD46FEC3FF0E11FE" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">paralectotype</typeStatus>
has the following data label: 97250 [printed]\ 1360 [handwritten]\ 
<specimenCount id="9D65FD11FFEAFFF6FEBCFE03FEB711DC" box="[338,357,410,433]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
[handwritten].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3796513FFEAFFF6FF44FE43FD91129E" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDC3698FFEAFFF6FF44FE43FD91129E" blockId="2.[170,796,474,755]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FF44FE43FEE3119E" bold="true" box="[170,305,474,499]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Comments:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FEADFE43FDC7119E" author="Schrottky, C." box="[323,533,474,499]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="330 - 613" refId="ref4893" refString="Schrottky, C. 1902 b. Ensaio sobre as abelhas solitarias do Brazil. Revista do Museu Paulista, 5: 330 - 613." type="journal article" year="1902">Schrottky (1902b)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFEAFFF6FF44FE63FF0E127E" box="[170,220,506,531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected on a 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFEAFFF6FD8DFE63FCC5127E" box="[611,791,506,531]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caesalpiniaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Caesalpiniaceae</taxonomicName>
, probably 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFEAFFF6FEF5FD83FE8D125E" box="[283,351,538,563]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FEF5FD83FE8D125E" box="[283,351,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cassia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. According to the accession book at MZSP the number 1,360 refers to the following data: “ 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FF5AFDC3FF26121E" box="[180,244,602,627]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FF10FDC3FEBC121E" box="[254,366,602,627]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, Rincão, 
<date id="FFDD1058FFEAFFF6FE21FDC3FDC8121E" box="[463,538,602,627]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1901-02">ii.1901</date>
, D. Ehrardt col” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FD21FDC3FEF712FE" author="Ramos, K. S. &amp; Kawada, R. &amp; Brandao, C. R." pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="335 - 361" refId="ref4707" refString="Ramos, K. S.; Kawada, R. &amp; Brandao, C. R. 2015. Type specimens of bees (Hymenoptera, Apidae) deposited in the Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Brazil. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 55 (24): 335 - 361. DOI" type="journal article" year="2015">
Ramos 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FF42FDE3FF3712FE" box="[172,229,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.,</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFEAFFF6FEDBFDE3FE0A12FE" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[309,472,634,659]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsata">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FEDBFDE3FE0A12FE" box="[309,472,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Centris dorsata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FD3EFDE3FCC812FE" box="[720,794,634,659]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FF5FFD03FE3212DE" box="[177,480,666,691]" country="Bolivia" name="Cochabamba" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Cochabamba department</collectingRegion>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FDD8FD03FDA012DE" box="[566,626,666,691]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FD64FD03FD1E12DE" box="[650,716,666,691]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FD0FFD03FE9712BE" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FEA1FD23FE3212BE" box="[335,480,698,723]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FE07FD23FDE512BE" box="[489,567,698,723]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FDAFFD23FD3712BE" box="[577,741,698,723]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FF45FD43FECA129E" box="[171,280,730,755]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
states) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FE9FFD43FDEB129E" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[369,569,730,755]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref4557" refString="Moure, J. S.; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. 2007. Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S.; Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.). Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region, Curitiba, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia. p. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FE2EFD43FE2B129E" box="[448,505,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.,</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
